  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing the Republic of Moldova&apos;s COVID-19 Preparedness and Urgent Response Capacity in the International Borders and Penitentiaries</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The global epidemic of COVID-19 poses a clear risk to the health and well-being of the people of the Republic of Moldova, considering the country&apos;s borders and internal migration dynamics. Preparing for the scenario of large numbers of returning citizens and crossing the borders of Moldova, in order to reduce the spread of the disease under the second wave of COVID-19, it is essential to support the efforts of frontline Border Police for screening for COVID-19 at the points of entry after re-opening in September 2020. There are overwhelming needs for personal protective equipment (PPE) such as gloves and mask, and for hand sanitizers and disinfection, as well as water and sanitation hygiene (WASH) related materials. The project will address the urgent need for procurement of urgently required PPE and other WASH supplies for the General Inspectorate of the Border Police (GIBP) and the National Administration of Penitentiaries, to maintain their ability to work in safe conditions, continue implementing the country&apos;s preparedness and response plan at borders, airports, and penitentiary institutions, as well prevent the spread of infectious disease among staff and among detained and imprisoned people.</narrative>
  </description>
